src_text: Nawumbisi wa Hundzuluxo wa Nawu wa Vugevenga (Maendlelo ya Vulavisisi) wa 2021
trg_text: Criminal Law (Forensic Procedures) Amendment Bill of 2021

src_text: Khabinete yi pasise ku rhumeriwa ka Nawumbisi wa Hundzuluxo wa Nawu wa Vugevenga (Maendlelo ya Vulavisisi) wa 2021 ePalamende ku ya phurosesiw Mihundzuluxo leyi ringanyetiweke yi lulamisela ndlela ya ku sindzisa ku tekiwa ka tisampulu ta le rhameni ta DNA (tisampulu kusuka eka tisele ta le ndzeni ka rhama ra munhu) kusuka eka vanhu lava va voniweke nandzu ehansi ka milandzu ya Xedulu ya 2.
trg_text: Cabinet approved the submission of the Criminal Law (Forensic Procedures) Amendment Bill of 2021 to Parliament for processin The proposed amendments provide for the mechanism to enforce the taking of DNA buccal samples (samples from cells on the inside of the person s cheek) from people convicted under Schedule 8 offence

src_text: Milandzu ya Xedulu ya 8 yi katsa milandzu ya swa masangu, vukhamba, ku ngungumerisiwa ka vanhu na ku dlaya hi ku tiyimisel Tisampulu ta le rhameni leti hlengeletiwaka ti ta humelerisa vuchuchisi bya nkarhi lowu taka eka vaonhi vo tlhandlamet
trg_text: Schedule 8 offences include sexual offences, robbery, human trafficking and culpable homicid The collected buccal samples will facilitate future prosecutions for reoffender

src_text: Nawumbisi lowu wu ta tlhela wu kotisa ku tumbuluxiwa ka databesi ya DNA ya vulavisisi byo angarhela ku tiyisa nyimpi ehenhla ka vugevenga hi ku nyika maphorisa vuswikoti hi vumbhoni bya ku lavisisa na ku ololoxa milandzu yo tivikan
trg_text: The Bill will also enable the establishment of a comprehensive forensic DNA database to strengthen the fight against crime by capacitating the police with evidence to investigate and solve serious crime
